article.headline: Harvard 69, Holy Cross 59
article.story: BOSTON -- Jeremy Lin scored 19 of his 30 points in the second half as Harvard defeated Holy Cross on Tuesday, 69-59. With Harvard up 53-52 with five minutes to play, Lin scored seven straight points to put the game away. Lin sported a bandage over his right eye for most of the game after getting scratched in the opening minutes, but still managed to hit 9-of-15 from the field, including 4-of-5 from 3-point range. He added nine rebounds, four steals and three assists. Keith Wright had 12 rebounds for Harvard (2-1). Greg McCarthy led Holy Cross with 18 points, eight rebounds and four steals. Eric Meister and R.J. Evans each added 10 points for Holy Cross (2-3) Harvard shot just 33 percent from the field but made 32 of 39 free throw attempts.
